    <!-- ABOUT STRINGS -->
    <string name="about_whatdoesitdo"><b>Goal:</b> Privacy Friendly WiFi-Manager keeps track of the cell tower ids in your area while you are connected to a Wi-Fi. By keeping this information, the app tries to learn
    where your WiFi is located without using GPS. The main goal is to avoid location tracking via Wi-Fi, but WiFi-Manager also saves battery life by automatically disabling your phones WiFi when it is not near a already known wireless network.
    </string>
    <string name="about_whyprivacyfriendly"><b>Privacy:</b> This privacy friendly app preserves your privacy by tracking least necessary data. All data is kept on your phone. No data is sent
        to anybody. We also try to use least permissions possible.
    </string>
    <string name="about_author"><b>Author:</b> Jan Henzel, Patrick Jauernig, Dennis Werner</string>
    <string name="about_affiliation">In affiliation with</string>
    <string name="about_privacyfriendly">This application belongs to the Privacy Friendly Apps Project.</string>
    <string name="about_moreinfo">More information can be found at:</string>
    <string name="about_secusourl"><a href="https://www.secuso.informatik.tu-darmstadt.de/en/research/results/privacy-friendly-apps">https://www.secuso.org</a></string>
    <string name="about_version">Version: %1$s</string>


    <!-- HELP STRINGS -->
    <string name="help_actionbar_string">Help</string>
    <string name="help_actionbar_substring_welcome">Welcome to Privacy Friendly WiFi-Manager</string>
    <string name="help_actionbar_string_basics">Help: Basics</string>
    <string name="help_actionbar_substring_step0">Step 1: Granting Permissions</string>
    <string name="help_actionbar_substring_step1">Step 2: Enabling the Manager</string>
    <string name="help_actionbar_substring_step2">Step 3: Adding a Wi-Fi</string>
    <string name="help_actionbar_substring_step3">Step 4: Delete a Wi-Fi</string>
    <string name="help_content_step0_description">A permission is needed to retrieve nearby cell information. To use location-based features of WiFi-Manager, starting with Android 6, you have to grant access to your coarse location. If you want to use this functionality later, you can request the necessary permission in the settings.</string>
    <string name="help_content_step1_description">To activate the WiFi-Manager, you have to enable it by toggling the on/off button. This enables its learning feature and collects the cell ids around your Wi-Fi. It also lets AutoWiFi take control of toggling your phone\'s Wi-Fi on/off.</string>
    <string name="help_content_step2_description">Now lets add a known WiFi to the list of managed WiFis. Touch the add-button on the bottom and then select a Wi-Fi in your range.</string>
    <string name="help_content_step3_description">To delete a Wi-Fi in your list, simply press a little longer on the Wi-Fi list. Then delete a Wi-Fi by pressing on the trashcan symbol beside its name.</string>
    <string name="help_welcome_description"><b>Welcome to Privacy Friendly WiFi-Manager!</b>\r\nThis app helps you automatically turning on/off your Wi-Fi while you are not near a known WiFi.\r\n\r\n<b>How it works:</b> While you are sitting in an area with a WiFi, you are surrounded by radio masts providing you a \'cell\'
        for your mobile phone. WiFi-Manager remembers which cell is near your Wi-Fi, to turn it right on when you are coming home, or turning it off, when you are leaving (e.g. work/school).\r\n\r\nBy using the schedule, you can also define time slots, when your phone\'s Wi-Fi should automatically be turned off (e.g. at night).\r\n\r\nTap \'start\' to take a tour.
    </string>

